title.narrative: Supporting Uganda’s Tuberculosis Reduction Strategy

description.narrative: Uganda - Tuberculosis - Ministry of Finance, Planning and Economic Development of the Republic of Uganda - MoFPED. This program has the following goals: To reach a reduction of 35% in TB Prevalence by 2020 (93/100,000).. The objectives of this program are: To strengthen systems for effective management of Tuberculosis & Leprosy services to meet the NSP targets. To detect 85% of estimated TB cases and successfully treat 90% of them by 2020. Provide TB/HIV integrated care to co-infected patients and enrol >90% on ART by 2020. To detect 80% of estimated DR-TB cases and treat successfully 80% of them by 2020
